Make your own map
It's easy to make your own map. Just follow these steps:

1. Choose an area.
Pan and zoom the map to an area or search by its name or address.


2. Decide what to show.
Choose a Basemap then Add layers on top of it.


3. Add more to your map.
Add map notes to draw features on the map.

Display descriptive text, images, and charts for map features in a pop-up.


4. Save and share your map.
Give your map a name and description then share it with other people.

Pick a tour to learn more about using the map viewer.

Add Layer from File x
Locate the file you want to import.
  • Shapefile (ZIP archive containing all shapefile files)
  • CSV or TXT files with optional address, place or coordinate locations (comma, semi-colon or tab delimited)
  • GPX (GPS Exchange Format)
  • GeoJSON (open standard format for simple geographical features)

Note, the file you are uploading might reach size limitations in your web browser (Internet Explorer 7 or 8). For optimum performance, consider upgrading or using a different web browser.
Tip: You can also drag and drop a CSV or GPX file from your desktop onto your map.
